So overall - if you’re willing to spend the extra money - I’d recommend the Logitech Rally every time. It’s about as good of a PC-based conf room system as you can buy (hopefully they integrate the software live speaker switching sometime soon).

But in the 2 most important areas - mic quality and camera quality - the Logitech Rally absolutely crushes the Poly Studio. The Poly Studio has a bit of a ‘large room’ audio sound (that I hate) and the camera image was a bit pixelated when zoomed into the far end of the table.
On the speaker output quality - both were roughly the same (not that you’re playing music out of the speaker often).

Poly definitely wins the ‘sexiness’ category as well as the software-based auto zooming to current speaker (that works really great and I suspect will become a standard feature of all conf cams). Also comes with all mounting brackets vs having to pay $150 for Rally brackets.

Poly Studio was $800 and Rally was $2k. Rally comes with separate speaker and mic extension while Studio is all-in-one. Logitech also comes with a ‘table hub’ (which adds ability to hard wire laptops into it - but adds unnecessary complexity and likely never used).
